description.narrative: Data for Child Health Priority countries have technical capacity to collect and disseminate quality data on child health for evidence based planning and decision-making at national and sub-national levels, which contributes to Child Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Every Child to Survive and Thrive By 2021, countries apply child-sensitive policies, innovative community-centered approaches and evidence, to implement development and humanitarian interventions at scale, that enable Every Child to Survive and Thrive

description.narrative: During 2021, UNICEF’s Digital Health & Information Systems Unit worked to support governments and partners in the collection, analysis and use of data – including in emergency settings – by strengthening routine data collection, health management and information systems, and introducing digital and geospatial technologies. The unit worked across sectors;to support countries to leverage digital and geospatial technologies for the COVID-19 vaccine roll-out. The unit led adigital health system landscapingin 18 countries, with 11 more in the pipeline for mapping and launched and piloted theCHW guidance on strategic information and service monitoring. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/03/2022
